武汉“白衣天使”的跨年夜。
Wuhan "white angel" the big year.
作者：张家振 来源：中国经营网。
Authors: Zhang Jiazhenyuan: China Operations Network.
本报记者 张家振 武汉报道1月24日，除夕夜。
Our reporter Zhang Jiazhen, Wuhan reported January 24, New Year's Eve.
一段华中科技大学同济医学院附属同济医院一线医护人员的“年夜饭”触动了众多人的心。
The dinner of front-line medical staff of Tongji Hospital of Tongji Medical College of Huazhong University of Science and Technology touched many people's hearts.
这段视频显示，10名身着标志性白大褂、戴着口罩、护目镜的医护人员齐声喊出“武汉加油”的口号。
The video shows 10 medical staff in iconic white coats, masks and goggles chanting "Wuhan refuels."
办公室桌子上只摆放着一些零食和半瓶可乐，这是他们今年的年夜饭。
There are only some snacks and half a bottle of Coke on the office table. It's their New Year's dinner this year.
华中科技大学同济医学院附属同济医院一线医护人员的“年夜饭”“不当英雄，也不当逃兵。
Huazhong University of Science and Technology Tongji Medical College affiliated with the front-line medical personnel "New Year's dinner" "Not hero, not deserter.
”奋战在武汉市第五医院一线的医护人员王媛写下了这样的感触。
"Wang Yuan, a medical worker on the front line of Wuhan Fifth Hospital, wrote about the experience.
在万家团圆之时，王媛正在值夜班，接诊发热病人。
At the time of her family reunion, Wang Yuan was on night duty, attending to febrile patients.
“人比较多。
"There are more people.
”在和《中国经营报》记者简短交流几句后，王媛又投入到繁忙的工作中。
After a brief exchange with the China Operator, Wang Yuan returned to her busy work.
奋战在防疫一线的王媛王媛只是除夕夜奋战在防疫一线的万千医护人员中的普通一员。
Wang Yuan, a battle against epidemic prevention, was just one of thousands of health care workers battling on New Year's Eve.
1月24日夜里11点多，武汉市第五医院的护士刘丽雯接到了单位打来的加班电话，医院在收隔离病人，需要去加班。
On January 24, more than 11: 00 p.m., Wuhan Fifth Hospital nurse Liu Liwen received a work-related telephone call, the hospital in isolation patients, need to work overtime.
刘丽雯从武汉市洪山区白沙洲某小区赶往医院，由于打不到车，最终在志愿者援助下赶往医院。
Liu Liwen from the Hongshan District of Wuhan City Peshao a small district to the hospital, because can not get a car, finally with the assistance of volunteers rushed to the hospital.
同样奋战在防疫一线的还有武汉市第九医院的谢青。
Also fighting in the front line of epidemic prevention is Wuhan ninth hospital Xie Qing.
尽管万分忙碌，但物资非常紧缺。
Despite the hustle and bustle, supplies are in short supply.
“没有护目镜和防护服，甚至没有饭吃，外卖也都停了。
"There were no goggles, no protective clothing, not even food, no take-out.
”谢青告诉记者，一些非正规渠道过来的社会捐赠物品，比如不是正规企业生产的物资也不敢用，担心有人恶意污染后医生护士会受到污染。
Xie told reporters that some donations from non-formal sources, such as materials not produced by formal enterprises, were too scared to use, fearing that doctors and nurses would be contaminated by malicious pollution.
奋战在防疫一线的医护人员团队一则武汉市第九医院院办的求助信息显示，现在很需要医疗物资，急缺防护服、护目镜和口罩，紧急求助各界人士捐助。
A team of medical personnel fighting in front of the epidemic prevention in Wuhan City, a hospital run by the 9th hospital of Wuhan, showed that there is a great need for medical supplies, urgent need of protective clothing, goggles and masks, people from all walks of life to donate.
对于这则求助信息的真实性，记者拨打求助电话无人接听。
For the authenticity of this help message, the reporter called the help line nobody answered.
一位不愿具名的武汉市第九医院工作人员向本报记者证实，求助电话和求助信息属实，确实存在医疗物资严重短缺情况。
A staff member of Wuhan's Ninth Hospital, who declined to be named, confirmed to the reporter that the calls and calls for help were true and that there was a serious shortage of medical supplies.
上述武汉市第九医院医护人员还告诉记者，国家拨款目前还没有，病人来看病，这个钱是医院自己垫付的，吃的喝的穿的用的很多物资也没有到位。
The above-mentioned Wuhan Ninth Hospital medical staff also told reporters that the state allocation is not yet available, patients came to see the doctor, the money was paid for by the hospital themselves, food, drink, and a lot of supplies were not in place.
今天被临时调往武汉市汉口医院的陈倩，主要负责照顾肺炎重症患者。
Chen Qian, who was temporarily transferred to Hankou Hospital in Wuhan today, is mainly responsible for taking care of severe pneumonia patients.
其同样告诉记者物资缺乏，“口罩、防护服、饭都得不到保障”。
It also told reporters that the lack of supplies, "masks, protective clothing, food are not guaranteed."
（应受访者要求，文中均系化名。
(At the request of the interviewee, the text is an alias.
照片由受访医护人员提供。
Photographs were provided by health professionals interviewed.
）（编辑：曹学平 校对：彭玉凤）。
